extends ./layout/default.jade

block variable
    - var chapter_num = "03"
    - var chapter_title_en = "I'm like you... I have no name"
    - var chapter_title_cn = "我跟你一樣⋯⋯ 沒有名字。"

block title
    title MGS #{chapter_num} - #{chapter_title_en} (#{chapter_title_cn})

block container
    h2.title.title-en
        span.title-num #{chapter_num}
        strong.title-en
            | #{chapter_title_en}
        strong.title-cn
            | #{chapter_title_cn}
    .movie
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Just what I'd expect from the man with the same code as the boss. It's been a long time since I've had such a good fight but I'm just getting warmed up. (Ocelot leaps out from behind the pillar ready to shoot but a cloaked figure jumps down from the ceiling and attacks him with a sword.  Ocelot's arm is cut off in the forearm.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What!  My hand!!! (The figure quickly slices down all of the wires connected to the C4 and the ropes binding Baker to the support pillar.  he falls to the ground as the C4 explodes around him.  Ocelot is thrown against the wall by the explosions.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaaaaaahhh!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Uuuunnhh!  Ooooof!  Stealth Camouflage, can't you even die right!? You were lucky, we'll meet again! (Ocelot runs out of the chamber as the figure reveals himself.  He is decked out as a cyborg ninja.  Snake levels his gun at him.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Who are you!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ninja
                | Ninja
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm like you... I have no name.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Ohhh... ohhhh!  That... that exoskeleton...! (The ninja ignores Baker and turns around to face Snake.  After a short time of staring each other down the ninja begins to convulse.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ninja
                | Ninja
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Ggggyyyaaaaaaahhh!!!  Ggggyyyyaaaaaaaahhh!!! Gggggyyyyyaaaaaaaaaaahhhh!!! (The ninja stops convulsing and hurries out of the room, jumping about. Snake holsters his weapon.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Who the hell!? (Snake helps Baker up to his feet.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Can you talk?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Who are you?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm not one of them.  The DARPA Chief told me he gave them his detonation code.  What about yours?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh, I get it.  Jim sent you... You... you're from the Pentagon.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Answer my question!  What about your code!?  There's no time!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I... talked.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What! Now the terrorists have both codes and can launch anytime!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's not like I didn't fight.  I managed to resist Psycho Mantis's mind probe.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He couldn't read you?  How'd you do it?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Surgical implants in my brain.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Surgical implants?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Kind of like a psychic insulation.  Everybody who knows these top-secret codes has it.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Even the DARPA Chief?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Of course.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | But the DARPA Chief said Mantis got his code by reading his mind.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Are you sure you heard him right?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yeah, I'm sure.  In that case, how did they get your code?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I never had any training on how to resist torture... (Baker coughs violently, he is obviously in very bad shape.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It looks like he had some fun with you all right.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He's not human.  I tell you, he loved every second of it.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What happened to your arm?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He broke it.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Looks like you're more than even now.  His was sliced off.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Ha. You're a funny man.  ...So... the DARPA Chief... is he okay?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Dead.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What!?  It can't be!  You know that's not what you promised, Jim! Now you want to shut me up! (Baker begins to whack Snake's leg with his cane.  Snake quickly calms him down.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Calm down!  What's wrong with you?  I just told you I was here to save you!  I didn't kill the DARPA Chief.  He had a heart attack or something.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | A heart attack? Oh, don't be a fool.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Anyway, the terrorists have both codes now.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Those boys are totally insane.  They wouldn't hesitate to launch.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I agree.  But what do they really want?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Who knows.  Maybe they're like us in the arms industry... always looking forward to the next good war.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Well I'm not going to let these maniacs start a war toady.  Do you still have the card keys.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Card keys?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | To override tge detonation codes!  I heard you had them...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No, not anymore.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What!?  Who does then!?  Not the terrorists!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No, that woman.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Woman!?  Who!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | A soldier that was thrown in prison along with me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | A female soldier?  It must be...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | She said that she had just joined up as a new recruit.  She said they threw her in prison because she refused to take part in the rebellion.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | A new recruit?  Could that be the Colonel's niece!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I gave her the key.  Looks like she managed to break out of here though. I hope she's okay.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm sure she is.  She's green... but as tough as they come.  But how did you know she escaped?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I was in contact with her by Codec.  Until I was tied up here that is.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Codec?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes.  She stole it from the guard.  If she still has it, you should be able to contact her.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm sure she still has it.  What frequency was she at?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh yeah.  Let me tell you.  It's... (Baker is struggling to remember.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...Oh... sorry... I forgot...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Damn!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh that's right!  It should be on the back of the CD case.  Try to contact her.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'll contact her right away.  But tell me... If this doesn't work, is there some other way to prevent the missile launch?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hmmm.  You need to find Hal Emmerich, one of my employees.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Who's that?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | The team leader of the Metal Gear Rex project.  A genius at engineering, but a little bit of an oddball.  If there is anyone who can figure out how to stop Metal Gear from launching, it's him.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What if he can't come up with anything?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You'll have to destroy it.  Emmerich knows how to destroy Metal Gear.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where is this Emmerich?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Well... he's probably being held somewhere in the Nuclear Warhead Storage Building.  It's north from here.  That's where he worked.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I understand, but... why Metal Gear?  The Nuclear Age ended with the turn of the millenium.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're wrong.  The threat of nuclear war isn't gone... in fact it's greater than it's ever been. (Scenes of missile launches, storage buildings, and missile silos are shown.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | The amount of spent nuclear fuel and plutonium is increasing even today.  Listen, have you ever seen a warehouse full of nuclear material?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...No.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Drums and drums of nuclear waste stacked this high.  As far as you can see because there's still no real way to dispose of the stuff.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So they just close the lid and pretend like it'll go away?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Essentially, yes.  And they're not even doing a good job of storing it.  Many of the drums are corroded... with nuclear waste seeping out of them.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Unbelievable.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Not only that, several pounds of MUF are reported every year.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | MUF?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It stands for "material unnacounted for". It proves that there is a large and well organized black market in nuclear materials. Furthermore, since the end of the Cold War, Russian nuclear engineers, in particular, are out of work with nowhere to turn. (We go back to the chamber where Snake and Baker are conversing.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | In other words, there is plenty of nuclear material and scientists for making a bomb.  We live in an age when any small country can have a nuclear weapons program.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What about the other superpowers?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Russia and China still maintain a signifigant nuclear presence. Complete nuclear disarmament is an impossibility.  To maintain our own policy of deterrance, we need a weapon of overwhelming power.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You mean Metal Gear.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You know our industry suffered quite a blow as a result of the cut-backs in military budgets, due to this so called "peace".
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I remember hearing a lot about mergers and take-overs among the big weapons makers.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes.  And after my company lost their bid to produce the Air Force's next fighter jet, the Metal Gear project was out last ace in the hole.  That's why we pushed to have Metal Gear developed as a black project.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Black project?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Secret projects paid for by the Pentagon's black budget.  You can avoid a lot of red tape a get a great lead-time on your weapons production.  And no one can bother you.  Not even those bleeding heart liberals on the military oversight committee.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Bribes.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I prefer to think of it as good buisness.  Anyway, Metal Gear was going to be formally adopted after the results of this exercise were analyzed.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't give a crap about you and your company.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes, that's about what I'd expect from a grunt like you... Here, this is what you came for, right? (Baker fishes a disc out of his pocket and hands it to Snake.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What's that?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | An optical disk.  It's all here.  The main hard drive was destroyed by gunfire.  This is the only remaining copy of the data.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What kind of data?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | All the data collected from this exercise.  Don't play dumb.  I know you were sent to get this.  I hid it from that sadistic maniac while he was torturing me.  They don't know that this disk exists. Make sure that you report this to Jim... to your boss.  I'll give you my card too.  It'll open up all level two security doors.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Can you walk?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...No ...You go on without me.  They got my password... they don't want anything else from me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I have one more question.  Who or what was that ninja thing?  It looked like you knew something.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-baker
                | Baker
                span :
